The paper proposes a deep learning approach for Magnetic Resonance Fingerprinting (MRF) recovery, which involves image reconstruction and quantitative mapping. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of dimensionality reduction and manifold enumeration, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of hierarchical matched-filters, which are commonly used in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and multimedia (cs.MM).
